---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Header from "../components/Header.astro";
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";
import Prose from "../components/Prose.astro";
import { site, absoluteUrl } from "../site.config";

const title = "Privacy Policy";
const description = `${site.name} privacy policy — your photos never leave your browser. What little data we collect, your rights under GDPR and CCPA, and how to contact us.`;

const privacySchema = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "WebPage",
  "@id": absoluteUrl("/privacy"),
  name: `${site.name} Privacy Policy`,
  url: absoluteUrl("/privacy"),
  description,
  isPartOf: { "@id": `${site.url}/#website` },
};

const breadcrumbSchema = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "BreadcrumbList",
  itemListElement: [
    { "@type": "ListItem", position: 1, name: "Home", item: absoluteUrl("/") },
    { "@type": "ListItem", position: 2, name: "Privacy Policy", item: absoluteUrl("/privacy") },
  ],
};

// Build-time "last updated" date — stable across a deploy, no client JS.
const lastUpdated = new Date().toLocaleDateString("en-US", {
  year: "numeric",
  month: "long",
  day: "numeric",
});
---

<Layout title={title} description={description} jsonLd={[privacySchema, breadcrumbSchema]}>
  <Header />

  <main class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 py-12 sm:px-6 sm:py-16">
    <nav class="text-sm text-[var(--color-fg-subtle)]" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
      <a href="/" class="hover:text-[var(--color-fg)]">Home</a>
      <span class="px-1.5">/</span>
      <span class="text-[var(--color-fg-muted)]">Privacy Policy</span>
    </nav>

    <header class="mt-6">
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight sm:text-5xl">Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-[var(--color-fg-subtle)]">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>
    </header>

    {/* The TL;DR — the technical reality, up top */}
    <div
      class="mt-8 rounded-xl border p-5"
      style="border-color: color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-accent) 30%, transparent); background-color: color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-accent) 8%, transparent);"
    >
      <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed text-[var(--color-fg)]">
        <strong>The short version:</strong> {site.name} edits your photos entirely
        inside your own browser. Your images are <strong>never uploaded</strong> to
        us or anyone else — there is no server that receives them. We don't have
        accounts, we don't store your photos, and we can't see what you erase.
        This page explains the little data that is involved anyway (basic,
        privacy-respecting analytics and, possibly, ads on info pages).
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-10">
      <Prose>
        <h2>1. Who we are</h2>
        <p>
          {site.name} ("we", "us", "the site") operates the website at
          <code>{site.domain}</code>, a free, browser-based tool for removing
          objects from photos. For any privacy question, contact us at
          <a href={`mailto:${site.contactEmail}`}>{site.contactEmail}</a>. We are
          the data controller for the limited information described below.
        </p>

        <h2>2. Your photos are processed locally and never uploaded</h2>
        <p>
          This is the core of how the tool works, so it comes first. When you
          open a photo in {site.name}:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>The image is loaded and processed <strong>entirely within your browser</strong>, on your own device.</li>
          <li>The AI model that erases objects runs locally (via WebGPU or WebAssembly). It is downloaded to your device and runs there.</li>
          <li>Your photo is <strong>never transmitted to our servers, a third party, or any cloud service.</strong> There is no upload step.</li>
          <li>We do not receive, store, log, or have any ability to view the images you edit.</li>
          <li>When you close or refresh the tab, the image is gone from memory. We keep no copy because we never had one.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          You can verify this yourself: open your browser's developer tools,
          switch to the Network tab, and erase something. You will see no
          outbound request carrying your image data.
        </p>

        <h2>3. Information we do collect</h2>
        <p>
          Because there are no accounts and no uploads, the data we touch is
          minimal:
        </p>
        <h3>a. Analytics</h3>
        <p>
          We may use a privacy-respecting analytics tool (such as Google
          Analytics 4) to understand aggregate, anonymous usage — for example,
          how many people visited a page, which country region they're in
          (approximate), and which browser they use. This helps us improve the
          site. This data is aggregated and is <strong>not</strong> used to
          identify you personally, and it never includes your photos. Analytics
          is only active in production and may be disabled entirely.
        </p>
        <h3>b. Server logs</h3>
        <p>
          The site is served as static files by our hosting provider
          (Cloudflare Pages). Like virtually all websites, the host may process
          standard technical request data (such as IP address and user-agent)
          to deliver pages and protect against abuse. We do not control or retain
          these logs beyond what the host provides.
        </p>
        <h3>c. Local storage on your device</h3>
        <p>
          To make the tool fast and able to work offline, your browser may cache
          the downloaded AI model and your preferences on your own device (using
          the Cache API, IndexedDB, or localStorage). This data stays on your
          device, is not sent to us, and you can clear it anytime via your
          browser settings.
        </p>

        <h2>4. Cookies and advertising</h2>
        <p>
          The tool itself does not require cookies to function. We may serve
          advertisements on informational pages (such as this one, the FAQ, or
          the comparison page) to help keep {site.name} free. We never place ads
          inside or interrupt the eraser.
        </p>
        <p>
          If we use a third-party ad network such as Google AdSense, that network
          may use cookies or similar technologies to serve and measure ads. Third
          parties, including Google, use cookies to serve ads based on a user's
          prior visits to this and other websites. Google's use of advertising
          cookies enables it and its partners to serve ads based on your visit to
          this and/or other sites. You can opt out of personalized advertising by
          visiting
          <a href="https://www.google.com/settings/ads" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Google Ads Settings</a>,
          and review options at
          <a href="https://www.aboutads.info/choices/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">aboutads.info/choices</a>.
          Where required by law, ads will be served in a non-personalized mode or
          subject to a consent prompt.
        </p>

        <h2>5. How we use information</h2>
        <p>We use the limited data above only to:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Operate, maintain, and improve the website;</li>
          <li>Understand aggregate usage trends;</li>
          <li>Keep the site secure and prevent abuse;</li>
          <li>Display advertising on informational pages (if enabled).</li>
        </ul>
        <p>We do not sell your personal information.</p>

        <h2>6. Your rights (GDPR, CCPA, and others)</h2>
        <p>
          Depending on where you live, you may have rights over your personal
          data, including the right to access, correct, delete, or restrict its
          processing, and the right to object to processing or data portability.
          Under the CCPA, California residents have the right to know what
          personal information is collected and to opt out of its sale (we do not
          sell personal information).
        </p>
        <p>
          Because we don't hold accounts or your photos, in most cases we simply
          have no personal data tied to you. For anything analytics- or
          host-related, or to exercise any right, email
          <a href={`mailto:${site.contactEmail}`}>{site.contactEmail}</a> and we
          will respond as required by applicable law.
        </p>

        <h2>7. Children's privacy</h2>
        <p>
          {site.name} is not directed at children under 13 (or the minimum age in
          your jurisdiction), and we do not knowingly collect personal
          information from them. Since the tool requires no account and collects
          no photos, there is no personal data for a child to provide.
        </p>

        <h2>8. Data retention and security</h2>
        <p>
          We retain the minimal analytics data only as long as needed for the
          purposes above. Because your photos are never uploaded, there is no
          image data for us to retain or secure. The site is served over HTTPS.
        </p>

        <h2>9. Third-party services</h2>
        <p>
          We rely on a small number of third parties to operate: our hosting
          provider (Cloudflare Pages), and optionally an analytics provider
          (Google Analytics) and an ad network (Google AdSense). Each has its own
          privacy policy governing the data they process.
        </p>

        <h2>10. Changes to this policy</h2>
        <p>
          We may update this policy from time to time. When we do, we'll revise
          the "last updated" date at the top. Material changes will be reflected
          on this page.
        </p>

        <h2>11. Contact</h2>
        <p>
          Questions about this policy or your data? Email
          <a href={`mailto:${site.contactEmail}`}>{site.contactEmail}</a>. You can
          also read our <a href="/terms/">Terms &amp; Conditions</a> or learn more
          on the <a href="/about/">About</a> page.
        </p>
      </Prose>
    </div>
  </main>

  <Footer />
</Layout>
